    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Coolant Pump</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Always fill the cooling system with the same type of coolant that was drained from the system. Do
                    not mix coolant types.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drain the cooling system. For additional information, refer to Cooling System Draining,
                Filling and Bleeding in this section.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the cooling fan.</para>
            <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 133 Nm (98 lb-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0303010" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0017222.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="224px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the accessory drive belt tensioner clockwise and remove the drive belt.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0303011" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0017225.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Using a suitable tool, use a hole in the coolant pump pulley to prevent the pulley from turning.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts and the coolant pump pulley.</para>
            <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 36 Nm (26 lb-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0303012" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020393.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts, the coolant pump and discard the O-ring seal.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Inspect the mating surfaces. Clean the sealing surfaces with metal surface prep.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Install a new O-ring seal. Lubricate the O-ring seal with petroleum jelly prior to
                        installation.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>To install, tighten to 23 Nm (17 lb-ft).</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0303013" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020394.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To install, reverse the removal procedure.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
